# Expense Tracker Application
DecodeLabs Python Internship — Project 2 | Batch 2026

---

## Overview

A command-line Expense Tracker application built with Python.
Users can enter expense amounts and the program adds them up
and displays the total amount spent.

---

## Features

- Add expense amounts one by one
- Running total shown after every entry
- Invalid input handled gracefully
- Negative amount validation
- Final total displayed on exit
- Type 'quit' to stop and see total

---

## Concepts Used

- Accumulator Pattern (total += expense)
- while loop
- if / elif / else
- try / except ValueError
- float() for decimal numbers
- Input validation
- Sentinel Value (quit to exit)

---

## How to Run

1. Clone the repo
2. Go to Project-2 folder
3. Run this command:

python expense_tracker.py

---

